    "body": "You can find more information about the problem from links of [this comment](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/14669#issuecomment-854757512).\r\n\r\nNormal behavior in such case would be returning `The transaction is underpriced` or `Insufficient funds for gas * price + value` error. But no error occurs. So client application think that everything goes well but later you find that tx was never created. Does it seems normal? I don't think so.",
