    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It is not possible for us to guarantee that a transaction submitted to geth via RPC will be accepted by other peers and/or miners. Even if the transaction is valid in every way, other nodes may still reject it because they have a different view of the tx fee market.\r\n\r\nYour own node will accept all formally valid transactions via RPC, and will continue to submit them to other peers as long as they are in the local pool. In fact, the pool has special handling for locally submitted transactions to ensure they are not evicted even if their fee amount is significantly below others.\r\n\r\netherscan.io will show the transaction before it is included *only if the tx makes it to their pool*, which is not guaranteed.\r\nIn order to ensure that your transactions will eventually be included, you can track every tx you send in your application, and resend with higher fees if you find the inclusion does not happen fast enough.",
