    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "N confirmations in blockchain world means that there are N blocks mined on top of the one containing your tx. Since there's a global set of miners, in PoW chains it can happen that some miners miner on top of one reality while other on another. Probabilistically they converge fast. The reason exchanges wait for 12 blocks is because they can go bankrupt if someone sends them tokens, sells them and 15 secs later the tx gets reorged out. \r\n\r\nYou don't need to \"check 12 times\". Depending on your threat model you might want to wait 1-2-12 blocks on top of the one you've first seen your tx in. ",
